      "date": "2018-03-20 14:26:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> The change looks correct, but I'm curious what lead you here?  The code has been doing it this way (with various cosmetic changes) since before the start of Git history.\n\nAuditing this code for LU-10800. The list handling in LNet is not as safe as it should be and some backwards list_add() have popped up in recent development.\n\n(I think this has been observed many times before, nut the world would be a safer place if list head and list entry were represented by distinct types.)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
